README.md:5:Keep track of your Claude.ai plan usage at a glance.
README.md:9:- **Real-time usage monitoring** - Track your 5-hour session, 7-day weekly, and Sonnet-specific usage limits
README.md:10:- **Menu bar integration** - Clean, colour-coded usage indicator that lives in your macOS menu bar
README.md:12:- **Pacing indicator** - Flame icon warns when you're using Claude faster than sustainable pace
README.md:14:- **Auto-refresh** - Automatic usage updates every 1 minute, 5 minutes, or 10 minutes
README.md:20:The menu bar icon changes colour based on your usage levels:
README.md:23:  <img src="docs/menubar-safe.png" width="260" alt="Menu bar - Safe usage">
README.md:28:When using Sonnet models, an additional indicator shows your Sonnet-specific usage:
README.md:31:  <img src="docs/menubar-sonnet.png" width="300" alt="Menu bar - Sonnet usage">
README.md:44:Configure your Claude session, refresh interval, icon style, and notification thresholds:
README.md:51:### Setup Wizard
README.md:54:  <img src="docs/setup-wizard.png" width="600" alt="First-time setup wizard">
README.md:72:2. The setup wizard will guide you through initial configuration
README.md:73:3. Import from a browser signed in to [claude.ai](https://claude.ai), or paste your session manually
README.md:74:4. The app validates your session and begins monitoring usage
README.md:76:### Claude Session Setup
README.md:78:Pinemeter can import your existing Claude session from local browser cookies. Sign in to [claude.ai](https://claude.ai) in a supported browser, then choose **Import from Browser** in the setup wizard or Settings.
README.md:80:Chrome, Arc, Brave, Edge, and other Chromium browsers may ask for browser Safe Storage Keychain access so Pinemeter can decrypt cookies. Safari cookies are protected by macOS and may require Full Disk Access.
README.md:82:If browser import is unavailable, paste your session manually. Pinemeter accepts either a raw `sk-ant-...` session key or a Cookie header containing `sessionKey=...`.
README.md:84:#### Manual Session Setup
README.md:86:Your Claude session key is stored in your browser cookies.
README.md:93:4. Find the `sessionKey` cookie (starts with `sk-ant-`)
README.md:101:4. Find the `sessionKey` cookie (starts with `sk-ant-`)
README.md:109:4. Find the `sessionKey` cookie (starts with `sk-ant-`)
README.md:114:- Monitor your usage at a glance with the colour-coded menu bar icon
README.md:120:Pinemeter exports usage data to `~/.pinemeter/usage.json` for use with external tools like Claude Code statusline scripts, shell prompts, or custom dashboards.
README.md:127:  "session_usage": {
